opie (2.32-7) unstable; urgency=low

  * It is libpam-opie, not libpam_opie
  * Make opie-server recommend libpam-opie (the description mentioned
    it's not very useful without it so we might as well make that more
    explicit).
  * Add libopie and libopie-dev packages.
  * No longer use dh_suidregister
  * Use debian/opie-client instead of debian/tmp
  * This means we can use debhelper in V3 mode as well
  * Add Build-Depends
  * Use only a single copyright file instead of keeping multiple copies
    in debian/
  * Bump Standards-Version to 3.5.4
  * all of above from Wichert Akkerman <wichert@wiggy.net>

 -- Michael Stone <mstone@debian.org>  Fri, 20 Jul 2001 09:07:56 -0400

